					Full Description



Vocera Communications, Inc., incorporated on February 16, 2000, is a provider of communication solutions for mobile workers in healthcare, hospitality, energy, education and other industries. The Company's segments include Product and Service. The Company's solutions include the Vocera Communication System, Vocera Care Experience, Vocera Engage integration platform, smartphone applications and its Experience Innovation Network.The Company's Vocera Communication System consists of a software platform that connects communication devices, including its hands-free, wearable, voice-controlled communication badges, and third-party mobile devices that use its software applications to become part of the Vocera system. The system transforms the way mobile workers communicate by enabling them to instantly connect through voice or text messaging with the right person simply by saying or selecting the name, function or group name of the person they want to reach, often while remaining at the point-of-care. The Company's Vocera Communication Platform contains an optimized speech recognition engine, call routing and management functionality, reporting and analytics tools, clinical directories and user profiles. Its communication badge is a wearable device weighing less than over two ounces that operates over customers' industry-standard wireless fidelity (Wi-Fi) networks. Its communication badge incorporates automatic diagnostic mechanisms that feed data on wireless network performance back to the software platform for reporting and diagnosis of problems.The Company's Vocera Collaboration Suite provides a multi-mode communications and collaboration experience; combining the calling, texting, alerting and content distribution capabilities of Vocera into a smartphone application. Its Vocera Secure Texting is an alternative to non-secure short message service (SMS) texting that enables Health Insurance Portability and Accountability (HIPAA)-compliance and includes its cloud-based Secure Texting application, extending the power of the Vocera Communication Platform to physicians and care teams that are located both inside and outside the hospital. The Company's Vocera Care Experience is a hosted software suite, which offers caregivers communication solutions that span the entire care continuum- before admission, during treatment and after discharge. Vocera Care Experience modules include Pre-Arrival Communication, Good to Go, Care Calls and Care Rounds.The Company's professional services help customers deploy, manage, update and/or expand their Vocera systems. The Company offers a range of services, including clinical workflow design, wireless assessment, solution configuration, training and project management, enabling customers to integrate its solutions. The Company also provides classroom and distance learning curricula for systems administrators, information technology (IT) professionals and clinical educators. The Company provides round the clock technical support to its customers through its support centers in San Jose, California; Fort Wayne, Indiana; Toronto, Canada; Knoxville, Tennessee and Reading, United Kingdom. Additional services, including an annual Remote System Health Assessment and biweekly technical Webinar education, are offered as project-based consulting or through its membership collaborative. The Experience Innovation Network is a membership program that collaborates with healthcare provider organizations to further the development of innovations and solutions. The Company provides classroom training, distance learning or customized courseware covering best practices, implementation and use of its solutions. Training courses are provided for systems administrators, IT professionals and industry-specific, end user educators.The Company competes with Cisco Systems, Ascom and Spectralink.

