Vocera Communications, Inc. Key Developments

Vocera Communications, Inc. Presents at 14th Annual Craig-Hallum Institutional Investor Conference, May-31-2017
May 3 17
Vocera Communications, Inc. Presents at 14th Annual Craig-Hallum Institutional Investor Conference, May-31-2017 . Venue: The Depot Renaissance Minneapolis Hotel, 225 Third Avenue South, Minneapolis, MN 55401, United States.


Vocera Communications, Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Second Quarter and Full Year 2017
Apr 27 17
Vocera Communications, Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported total revenue of $36.30 million against $26.78 million a year ago. Loss from operations was $6.47 million against $3.66 million a year ago. Loss before income taxes was $6.26 million against $3.49 million a year ago. Net loss was $6.64 million or $0.24 per basic and diluted share against $3.58 million or $0.14 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Non-GAAP adjusted LBITDA was $0.555 million against $0.385 million a year ago. Non-GAAP net loss $1.52 million or $0.05 per basic and diluted share against $0.85 million or $0.03 per basic and diluted share a year ago.

The company provided earnings guidance for the second quarter and full year 2017. For the quarter, the company expects revenue of $36 million to $38 million, GAAP net loss of $8.0 million to $6.5 million, Non-GAAP net loss of $2.1 million to $0.7 million, loss per share of $0.28 to $0.23, diluted non-GAAP net loss per share of $0.08 to $0.03 and adjusted EBITDA of $1.0 million to $0.40 million. 

For the full year, the company expects revenue of $154 million to $161 million, GAAP net loss of $22.6 million to $16.5 million, Non-GAAP net income of $0.5 million to $5.5 million, GAAP net loss per share, basic and diluted of $0.79 to $0.58, diluted non-GAAP net loss per share of $0.02 to $0.19 and adjusted EBITDA of $5.0 million to $10.0 million.


Vocera Communications, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jun 02, 2017
Apr 21 17
Vocera Communications, Inc., Annual General Meeting, Jun 02, 2017, at 10:00 Pacific Standard Time. Location: 525 Race Street San Jose, CA 95126 United States Agenda: To elect three Class II directors to serve a three-year term through the third annual meeting of stockholders following this meeting and one Class I director to serve a two-year term through the second annual meeting of stockholders following this meeting, and until, in each case, a successor has been elected and qualified or until earlier resignation or removal; to ratify the appointment of Deloitte & Touche LLP as independent registered public accounting firm for the fiscal year ending December 31, 2017; and to consider and vote upon such other business as may properly come before the meeting or any adjournment or postponement thereof.


