Vocera B3000n Badge Data Sheet
The award-winning Vocera Badge is powered by the Vocera Communication Platform, which enables intelligent call routing based on name, role, availability and shift changes, ensuring the right information reaches the right person at the right time, in the right place.



 
Key Features


Weighs Less Than 2 oz. (53.9 g)
Lightweight, wearable design ensures the badge is readily available and easy to use.



 



Voice-Controlled, One-Button Operation
Hands-free, voice-controlled calling allows staff to keep working while communicating.


 


Durability
Rugged design and reinforced structure provide durability in mission-critical mobile environments.



 



Wireless Performance
Dual-band Wi-Fi radio provides advanced connectivity and delivers high-quality voice recognition.


 


Acoustic Performance
A four microphone design, high-quality speaker, and integrated acoustic noise reduction (ANR) improve audio clarity and decreases interference from background conversations and other sounds to improve speech recognition in noisy environments.



 



Usability

Dual band Wi-Fi radio supports both 2.4GHz and 5GHz frequencies and offers superior connectivity, high voice quality and excellent speech recognition.
High-contrast OLED display on the front of the badge facilitates ease of readability.
Smart battery and charger technology simplifies battery management.
Do-not-disturb button eliminates interruptions when necessary.
Headset jack facilitates private conversations.
Illuminated halo around call button provides visual status.



 


Antibacterial
BioCote® antimicrobial technology inhibits the growth of microorganisms
View Demonstration »



 


We use Vocera for all of our associates and feel it improves our response times to our patients and is an effective communication device between our providers and clinical staff.
Steve McCarty, Clinical Director, Health Management Associates, Inc.


 

Related Links
Vocera Communication Platform
Vocera solutions run on our enterprise-class platform that provides a secure, scalable and integrated communication system so physicians, clinicians and staff – both inside and outside the hospital – can deliver quality care across the patient journey.
Vocera Clinical System Integrations
Vocera integrates with more than 120 clinical systems such as EHRs, nurse call, patient monitoring, patient flow, interactive patient engagement, and real-time location systems to enable critical information exchange, improve operational efficiency and patient experience.
Wearables & Devices
Vocera supports a wide range of mobile devices for our applications, enabling organizations to choose the right device to best suit their operating environment. We have you covered whether your needs are for hands-free communication, image-rich devices optimized for viewing cardiac ECGs, or support for a BYOD policy. 

 


